description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OPERATIONAL SUPPORT MANAGER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUTPATIENTS &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£31,365 - £37,890 per annum/pro rata (AfC Band 6)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;37.5 hours per week – 12 MONTHS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT OPPORTUNITY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Vacancy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in Barnsley Hospital’s Outpatient department at a time of innovation and transformation. This is a new and key role to ensure the provision of an efficient, professional and a complex range of corporate services.  You will be responsible for leading on the scheduling of outpatient clinics, to work closely with nursing staff to ensure that departments run efficiently, provide day to day operational management of the Service providing direct supervision to the Department Managers. You will be a highly competent, knowledgeable and visible manager within our departments and will lead by example and inspire the teams to deliver exemplary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barnsley Hospital is committed to the transformation of outpatient services to provide care for the 21st century patient pathway using digital technology to support care delivery. You will be expected to be an active participant in the transformation work streams to support the delivery of modernisation work relating to clinic scheduling, medical records digitalisation and outpatient booking services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, the Service provides the telecommunication and administrative functions across general office and switchboard with responsibility for the Access to Health Records, Bereavement office, Cashiers, post room and Overseas Eligibility services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer a friendly working environment with the opportunity to learn new skills and continuous professional development. We will also offer the opportunity to work in a changing climate and be involved in transformation at local and regional levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a highly motivated and enthusiastic individual to join our friendly, dynamic multidisciplinary team. Candidates will need to be confident, motivated and flexible and have excellent communication skills. You will have high standards and be enthusiastic about participating in change with a positive attitude towards working in different ways. You must have an understanding of resource management, health and safety, risk and quality issues and RTT patient pathway and ERS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please relate your experience to the person specification in the job description when completing your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact: Sam Harper,  Head of Service/Professional Lead for Nursing &lt;strong&gt;Direct Line:&lt;/strong&gt; 01226 435690 &lt;strong&gt;Email: sam.harper3@nhs.net   &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is committed to promoting equality of opportunity and fair treatment to all applicants regardless of race, nationality, ethnic origin, gender, marital status, mental or physical disability, religion or belief, sexual orientation, age or offending history.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE: all correspondence regarding this vacancy and the interview process will be sent by e-mail.&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;Therefore, you are advised to check your emails/NHS Jobs account regularly following the closing date.   To speed up the recruitment process please ensure that your references are appropriate and where possible you have provided an email address and telephone number.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS).  The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges for adverts placed from 1st June are as follows:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that these charges are not applicable for roles band 5 and below. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standard Check:    £23.00 + Administration cost of £3.69 = deduction from salary as a one off payment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enhanced Check:  £40.00 + administration cost of £3.69 = £13.69 deduction from 1st months’ salary, £10.00 deduction from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date for applications: 19&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview to be held on: TBC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;If you wish to apply for this post, please visit NHS Jobs website and quote Ref No: 163-3570E-11-20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please refer to the attached additional document when completing your application, this will inform you about Values Based Recruitment at Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
